<reference id="r_fabric_types">
  <title>Fabric types</title>
  <shortdesc> This reference topic provides descriptions of common fabric types, their characteristics, and suggested washing ways.
  </shortdesc>

  <table>
        <title>Fabric Types and Characteristics</title>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Fabric Type</entry>
              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>Cotton</entry>
              <entry>
                Cotton is a natural fiber that is soft, breathable, and widely used in clothing, home textiles, and linens. It is known for its comfort and absorbency.
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Wool</entry>
              <entry>
                Wool is a natural fiber obtained from sheep and other animals. It is warm, insulating, and commonly used in sweaters, coats, and cold-weather gear.
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Silk</entry>
              <entry>
                Silk is a luxurious natural fiber known for its smooth texture and sheen. It is often used in fine clothing, scarves, and bedding.
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Polyester</entry>
              <entry>
                Polyester is a synthetic fabric that is durable, wrinkle-resistant, and easy to care for. It is often used in activewear, outerwear, and home textiles.
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Linen</entry>
              <entry>
                Linen is a natural fiber made from flax plants. It is cool, breathable, and typically used in summer clothing, tablecloths, and napkins.
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Denim</entry>
              <entry>
                Denim is a sturdy cotton twill fabric commonly used in jeans, jackets, and other durable clothing. It is known for its ruggedness and classic style.
              </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section>
  </refbody>
</reference>
     


  </refbody>
</reference>